## $\varepsilon$-edge Differential Privacy (DP) for Graphs


:::: {}

:::{.center}
<!-- [![](imgs/dp/dp.png){width=100%}]{scale=1.5} -->
![](imgs/dp/dp-edge.svg){width=50%}
:::

::: {.small .center}
A **randomized algorithm** [$\A_{\varepsilon}: \G^n \rightarrow \G^n$]{.dblue} satisfies $\varepsilon$-edge differential privacy if
$$
\boxed{\pr\pa{\color{red}{\A_{\varepsilon}(G_1) \in S}} \le e^\e\  \pr\pa{\color{green}{\A_{\varepsilon}(G_2) \in S} }\phantom{\frac{1}{2}}}
$$
for all $\color{red}{G_1 = (V, E_1)} \sim \color{green}{G_2=(V,E_2)}$ and $\color{red}{E_1} \Delta \color{green}{E_2}=1$
:::


